# Copy to ~/.config/dev-runner/dispatch.env and `chmod 600`. NOT committed — holds the shared secret.
#
# The bearer token n8n must send (generate a long random one; the same value goes in the n8n HTTP node).
DISPATCH_TOKEN=CHANGE_ME_long_random_shared_with_n8n
#
# Bind to an interface the n8n CONTAINER can reach — a docker bridge gateway, NOT 127.0.0.1.
# Find the gateway of the docker network the n8n container is on. VERIFY for this host:
#   docker inspect <n8n-container> --format '{{range .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{.Gateway}} {{end}}'
DISPATCH_BIND=REPLACE_WITH_DOCKER_BRIDGE_GATEWAY
DISPATCH_PORT=8770
#
# The spawned dev-runner needs these on PATH (claude, gh, git); the service env is otherwise minimal.
PATH=/home/REPLACE_RUNNER_USER/.local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
#
# No DEFAULT_REPO: dispatch is fail-closed. The repo comes from the request payload
# (n8n reads each issue's repository); a request without an explicit owner/name repo never builds.
#
# Pool -> credential seam (issue #40): each models.toml entry names a quota_pool (the shared rate/
# spend ceiling it draws from). For a pool "<pool>", the runner looks up YR_POOL_<POOL_UPPER_SNAKE>
# (hyphens become underscores) here to select that stage's claude credential/config directory —
# CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is set to the value for the duration of that one `claude -p` call. Unset ->
# ambient default (today's single-account behavior; nothing overridden). Both shipping entries
# (sonnet, opus) use quota_pool = "anthropic-main", so this is NAMED but not yet exercised — no
# variable is set below, and none needs to be until a second pool/account is provisioned.
# YR_POOL_ANTHROPIC_MAIN=/home/REPLACE_RUNNER_USER/.claude-pool-anthropic-main
#
# Shadow review seat (issue #165): a non-gating SECOND verdict on every gating review round, landed on
# the PR trail as an inert "YR-SHADOW-REVIEW: <verdict>" comment — never the review gate, terminal
# approval, or the merge evaluator. Dark by default: BOTH keys below must be set, or the runner behaves
# byte-identically to today (no shadow subprocess, no shadow artifact, no shadow comment). Operator-set;
# no default is provided.
# YR_SHADOW_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# YR_SHADOW_BASE_URL=https://api.example-provider.test/v1
